 located in the state of Kerala. It is common practice to respect the deity in each shape and form, such as Maha Saraswathi in the morning, Maha Lakshmi at noon, and Sri Durga in the evening-during the day in this temple. 2. Mandala Beach House and Resorts The cosy Mandala Cottage comprises one bedroom and can sleep up to three guests. This property is ideal for use as a therapeutic gateway because it is located amidst greeneries paddy fields and bordered by palm trees, bamboo, and banana trees. Customers are offered food that is both nourishing to the body and satisfying to the palate, creating an experience that is hard to forget. A large selection of food is available, ranging from the traditional cuisine of Kerala to dishes from other parts of the world. Everything is carried out with extreme caution while preserving hygiene and cleanliness. The fruits and vegetables sold here have not been treated with any chemicals. There are many different types of games available to play, including chessboard, playing poker, caroms, and Pallankuzhi. 3. Mary's Forane Church St. Mary's Church, which can trace its roots back to 835 A.D., is a well-known destination among deeply spiritual people. The location is well-known for the many religious gatherings that occur throughout the year, regardless of the season. The church has become a destination of pilgrimage for people from all over the world in the modern era. This is the location you should go to if you have a spiritual nature and are interested in learning more about the way of life and traditions practised by Christians. The church is also well-known for organising the most important feasts and festivals throughout the year, particularly in March. St. Sebastian's Feast is a well-known celebration in the church during March when you will be in Alappuzha. The festival is distinguished by the mesmerising effects of fireworks, which are accompanied by an abundance of vibrant colours and a wide variety of people. The incredible decorations, the magnificent appearance of the site, and the lavish feast make this location one of the city's most desirable places. 4. Alappuzha Beach If you enjoy being at the beach, then the captivating beauty of Alappuzha is something you cannot skip. One of the most well-known beaches in the region, Alappuzha beach is a major draw for visitors to the city of Alappuzha. Alappuzha Beach is one of the greatest beaches to visit during your vacation since it is less crowded than other beaches, has beautiful scenery, is peaceful, and has an appealing atmosphere. The lush palm trees, spiritual tranquillity of the adjacent park, freshwater rivers and the gorgeous Arabian Sea are exactly what you need to spend some minutes in peace. It doesn't matter whether you're on your honeymoon, travelling with your family, or venturing out on your own; this spot in God's land, Kerala, is a definite must-see for anybody who enjoys the aquatic wealth of the state. A wide variety of exciting activities are available, such as parasailing, beach volleyball, and surfing, for those who have a passion for the outdoors and adventurous pursuits. 5. Kuttanad Backwaters The real charm of Alappuzha may be found in its many bodies of water, but the backwaters of Kuttanad are the ones that have gained the greatest reputation throughout the years. The Kuttanad backwaters, commonly known as the "Rice bowl of Kerala," are considered one of the most attractive tourist destinations in the Alappuzha region. Due to the breathtaking scenery, this is among the most popular tourist destinations in the Alappuzha district. It is among the rare places to visit in India where agriculture is done 10 ft below sea level, making it the lowest altitude in the country. Therefore, the Backwaters of Kuttanad are among the must-visit tourist spots in Alappuzha. One of the most popular things in Alappuzha is to take a boat ride through the Kuttanad backwaters while taking in the breathtaking scenery of the waters surrounded by coconut palms. The houseboats are the superior option because they provide comfortable and pleasant facilities, allowing you to take full advantage of this location and have a more satisfying experience overall. Rice barges or houseboats are recommended to get the most out of your time on this body of water. 6. Karumadikkuttan One of the best places to go in Alappuzha to seek the divine blessings of Buddha is a well-known pilgrim centre known for its tranquil atmosphere. Karumadikkuttan is the name of a marble statue of Lord Buddha that can be found in Karumadi, which is not far from Alappuzha. The locals have given it this name because the statue here is dark in colour. The statue is notable for several reasons. One is that it is missing the left side entirely because it contains such a stunning example of Buddhist architecture; Alappuzha is a popular destination for people seeking spiritual fulfilment through vacationing. The statue was discovered and retrieved by the Archeological Association of India, and it is now housed in a secure enclosure close to the Karumadi Canal. The people who live in and around Karumadi have a strong desire to seek blessings from the statue because they believe it possesses the ability to provide severe healing to those who look upon it. Despite this, it is still going to be kept safe because of the withered state it is currently in. 7. Krishnapuram Palace The Krishnapuram Palace is a one-of-a-kind example of the architecture characteristic of the state of Kerala. Its gabled, low roofs and winding corridors make it a fascinating sight. Due to its proximity to the Krishnaswamy Temple and its construction in the traditional style of Kerala, the palace is widely considered the state's most popular tourist destination. This palace's accurate construction date could not be determined, but the Archeology Department notes that it is now considered a protected monument because of its historical significance. This palace serves as an archaeological museum. Its most noteworthy exhibit is a mural painting that spans 49 square meters and is titled Gajendra Moksham, which translates to "the salvation of the elephant king." In addition to these works of art, a lushly landscaped garden within the palace's compound should also be visited. 8. Marari Beach Marari Beach is among the best places to visit in Alappuzha for vacations with friends and family because it is beautiful and features golden sands and coconut palm trees. Marari beach will provide an entirely new experience of walking around the stunning and marvellous seashore. The area surrounding Marari Beach is home to several magnificent resorts and hotels renowned for providing exceptional hospitality to tourists. Individuals searching for an escape from the stress and chaos of their everyday lives and who want to be closer to the ocean will find this the ideal destination. In addition to its breathtaking panoramas of the ocean, the coastal area is home to several Ayurvedic treatment centres. The soothing treatments offered at these spas will make you feel as if all of your concerns are melting away into thin air. The peace of Marari beach is one reason Allepey is so well-known. It is the ideal destination for spending time with relatives or having a memorable honeymoon with your loved one. 9. Mullakkal Rajarajeswari Temple The Mullakkal Rajarajeswari Temple, also known as the Mullakkal Bhagavathy Temple, is a holy temple included on the list of Places to Visit in Alleppey to increase one's level of spirituality. The worship of the goddess Durga is the primary focus of this particular temple. Apart from Goddess Durga, other deities are also worshipped here, for example, Lord Hanuman, Lord Ayyappa, Lord Krishna, Lord Ganesha, Nagaraja, and the Navagraha. This temple in Alappuzha is an essential destination for everyone seeking enlightenment and God's favour. Devotees believe this temple was constructed about five hundred years ago, making it one of the most desirable locations in the paradise of backwaters Alappuzha. Temple visits are most enjoyable during the winter months of November and December. The primary cause for this is the great festival of Mullakkal Chirappu, which lasts for 41 days (about 6 weeks), and devotees participate in large numbers throughout this time. 10. Vembanad Lake This particular lake is not only the biggest but also the longest of those that can be found in Kerala. When it comes to enjoying backwater tourism in Alappuzha, one of the greatest spots is Vembanad Lake. Vembanad lake, located in the middle of Kerala, is surrounded by mangrove and coconut tree forests. The Vembanad Lake is the largest lake and the only one that never stops flowing since it is fed by a network of smaller lakes that all flow into it at some point. However, the fact that the massive area is so long is not what draws travellers to the location in the first place. Throughout the annual Onam festival, this lake is the sole venue for the world-famous boat race during the celebration. This is the ideal location to spend quality time with your family while enjoying some delicious fresh seafood. Boating on Vembanad Lake and spending the night on a houseboat, there is a one-of-a-kind experience that ranks high on the list of recommended activities for visitors to the Alappuzha region. This is one of the most well-liked places to spend a holiday in all of Kerala. Conclusion In addition to these recommended sights to see in Alleppey, the city is also famous for its houseboats and backwaters. Alappuzha is just the image that one would like to have in front of his eyes at all times. This magnificent town is a sight to see and is deserving of one's awe and respect. There are a greater number of churches and temples. November to March is ideal for travel to Alappuzha because of the pleasant weather. The weather at this time is ideal for the visitors to come and enjoy themselves. After the monsoon, this location transforms into a spot completely dominated by nature. This town in Kerala is sometimes referred to as the "Venice of the East." It is home to several Alappuzha tourist destinations, making it well worth the trip. Next TopicTourist Places in Kozhikode ? prev next ? For Videos Join Our Youtube Channel: Join Now Feedback Send your Feedback to [email protected] Help Others, Please Share Learn Latest Tutorials Splunk SPSS Swagger Transact-SQL Tumblr ReactJS Regex Reinforcement Learning R Programming RxJS React Native Python Design Patterns Python Pillow Python Turtle Keras Preparation Aptitude Reasoning Verbal Ability Interview Questions Company Questions Trending Technologies Artificial Intelligence AWS Selenium Cloud Computing Hadoop ReactJS Data Science Angular 7 Blockchain Git Machine Learning DevOps B.Tech / MCA DBMS Data Structures DAA Operating System Computer Network Compiler Design Computer Organization Discrete Mathematics Ethical Hacking Computer Graphics Software Engineering Web Technology Cyber Security Automata C Programming C++ Java .Net Python Programs Control System Data Mining Data Warehouse Javatpoint Services JavaTpoint offers too many high quality services. Mail us on [email protected], to get more information about given services. Website Designing Website Development Java Development PHP Development WordPress Graphic Designing Logo Digital Marketing On Page and Off Page SEO PPC Content Development Corporate Training Classroom and Online Training Data Entry Training For College Campus JavaTpoint offers college campus training on Core Java, Advance Java, .Net, Android, Hadoop, PHP, Web Technology and Python. Please mail your requirement at [email protected] Duration: 1 week to 2 week Like/Subscribe us for latest updates or newsletter Learn TutorialsLearn JavaLearn Data StructuresLearn C ProgrammingLearn C++ TutorialLearn C# TutorialLearn PHP TutorialLearn HTML TutorialLearn JavaScript TutorialLearn jQuery TutorialLearn Spring Tutorial Our WebsitesJavat