s of fireworks, which are accompanied by an abundance of vibrant colours and a wide variety of people. The incredible decorations, the magnificent appearance of the site, and the lavish feast make this location one of the city's most desirable places. 4. Alappuzha Beach If you enjoy being at the beach, then the captivating beauty of Alappuzha is something you cannot skip. One of the most well-known beaches in the region, Alappuzha beach is a major draw for visitors to the city of Alappuzha. Alappuzha Beach is one of the greatest beaches to visit during your vacation since it is less crowded than other beaches, has beautiful scenery, is peaceful, and has an appealing atmosphere. The lush palm trees, spiritual tranquillity of the adjacent park, freshwater rivers and the gorgeous Arabian Sea are exactly what you need to spend some minutes in peace. It doesn't matter whether you're on your honeymoon, travelling with your family, or venturing out on your own; this spot in God's land, Kerala, is a definite must-see for anybody who enjoys the aquatic wealth of the state. A wide variety of exciting activities are available, such as parasailing, beach volleyball, and surfing, for those who have a passion for the outdoors and adventurous pursuits. 5. Kuttanad Backwaters The real charm of Alappuzha may be found in its many bodies of water, but the backwaters of Kuttanad are the ones that have gained the greatest reputation throughout the years. The Kuttanad backwaters, commonly known as the "Rice bowl of Kerala," are considered one of the most attractive tourist destinations in the Alappuzha region. Due to the breathtaking scenery, this is among the most popular tourist destinations in the Alappuzha district. It is among the rare places to visit in India where agriculture is done 10 ft below sea level, making it the lowest altitude in the country. Therefore, the Backwaters of Kuttanad are among the must-visit tourist spots in Alappuzha. One of the most popular things in Alappu